1
00:01:11,320 --> 00:01:11,880
Make way.

2
00:01:14,520 --> 00:01:15,120
Inspector Huang.

3
00:01:15,360 --> 00:01:16,200
You're finally here.

4
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:22,280
Where is Master Lin?

5
00:01:22,720 --> 00:01:24,520
After the Master saw Second Madam's body,

6
00:01:24,520 --> 00:01:25,480
he fainted.

7
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,160
He hasn't woken up yet.

8
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:30,160
Chuncheng.

9
00:01:38,920 --> 00:01:39,920
This ominous thing

10
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:41,240
has claimed another life.

11
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:44,200
Whose room is this?

12
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:45,160
This is

13
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:46,920
the room Madam Bai lived in before she died.

14
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:47,680
Then,

15
00:01:49,080 --> 00:01:50,280
who is this?

16
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:51,400
It's

17
00:01:51,920 --> 00:01:52,600
Second Madam.

18
00:01:53,160 --> 00:01:54,080
Second Madam?

19
00:01:55,080 --> 00:01:55,920
Then why

20
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:57,560
is she wearing this opera costume?

21
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:58,520
No, no, no, no, no.

22
00:01:59,160 --> 00:01:59,840
When we arrived,

23
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:01,360
Second Madam was already like this.

24
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:03,120
I also don't know

25
00:02:03,440 --> 00:02:04,000
why

26
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:06,120
the opera costume I personally locked

27
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:07,080
in the storeroom cabinet

28
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:08,200
ended up on her.

29
00:02:08,720 --> 00:02:09,680
Locked in the cabinet?

30
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:11,680
I remember Second Madam yesterday

31
00:02:11,880 --> 00:02:13,240
asked you to give her the costume.

32
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:14,800
Why lock it in the storeroom?

33
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:16,720
I gave it to her originally.

34
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:17,840
But the Master,

35
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:18,760
after returning yesterday,

36
00:02:19,720 --> 00:02:20,560
for some unknown reason,

37
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:21,720
took it back from

38
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:22,680
Second Madam's hands.

39
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:24,760
He said it was involved in Judou

40
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:26,000
and Chunxiao's murder cases,

41
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,080
and told me to keep it safe.

42
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:28,200
I even thought

43
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:29,400
it was under your orders.

44
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:30,600
Steward Lai!

45
00:02:32,440 --> 00:02:32,960
Steward Lai!

46
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:33,960
The Master is awake.

47
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:35,440
He heard Inspector Huang is here,

48
00:02:35,640 --> 00:02:37,120
and asked you to invite them to the living room.

49
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:45,880
Inspector Huang.

50
00:02:46,920 --> 00:02:47,920
Sorry to trouble you again.

51
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:49,520
You're too polite, Master Lin.

52
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:50,720
But you,

53
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:52,840
you should take good care of your health.

54
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:55,280
Master Lin.

55
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:57,720
How did you find

56
00:02:57,720 --> 00:02:58,720
Second Madam's body?

57
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:03,760
Inspector Huang,

58
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,480
last night when I was patrolling,

59
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:06,640
I vaguely

60
00:03:06,880 --> 00:03:07,880
heard in the building again

61
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:09,440
a woman singing opera.

62
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:13,880
I noticed

63
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:15,800
a fire in Madam Bai's room.

64
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:23,320
Help!

65
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:24,160
Fire!

66
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:25,960
By the time we arrived

67
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:27,280
and put out the fire,

68
00:03:27,640 --> 00:03:28,920
Second Madam was already dead.

69
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:30,520
But the strange thing is,

70
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,000
everything in the room,

71
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,640
including the opera costume on Second Madam,

72
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:36,120
was completely intact.

73
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:37,600
But she just...

74
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:38,960
she just...

75
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:41,400
Master,

76
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:43,680
that ghost costume is truly evil!

77
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,680
Lai Fu begs you to burn it!

78
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:47,680
This time it took away two maids

79
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:48,400
and Second Madam.

80
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,480
It definitely won't stop here.

81
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:51,400
Shut up!

82
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:53,720
Don't spout such

83
00:03:53,720 --> 00:03:54,560
nonsense in front of Inspector Huang.

84
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:56,120
It's just an ordinary opera costume.

85
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:01,960
Officer Li.

86
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:02,600
Master Lin.

87
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:07,000
How is it?

88
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,440
Under the deceased's costume,

89
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:12,840
I found this fabric fragment.

90
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:15,400
Besides a burnt smell on it,

91
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:16,960
there's also a scent

92
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:18,240
like garlic,

93
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:19,560
and a bit like

94
00:04:19,840 --> 00:04:20,480
stinky fish.

95
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:21,840
I suspect

96
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:23,000
someone sprinkled

97
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:24,000
white phosphorus powder on it.

98
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:30,720
Moreover,

99
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:32,160
according to the preliminary examination,

100
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:33,920
the deceased's mouth, nose, and throat

101
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:35,040
all show extensive

102
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,480
burn marks from smoke and fire.

103
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:38,560
That is to say,

104
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:39,640
the deceased

105
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:42,200
wasn't sprinkled with white phosphorus after death,

106
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:43,880
but while she was alive,

107
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:45,720
her clothes had already been tampered with.

108
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:46,320
Exactly.

109
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,360
But the smell of white phosphorus is so strong,

110
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,440
how could she not smell it?

111
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:55,280
I'm wondering about that too.

112
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:56,400
Right.

113
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,520
On this fragment,

114
00:04:58,840 --> 00:04:59,320
I also found

115
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:00,560
marks of it being cut by a sharp object.

116
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:01,520
Here.

117
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:10,680
On this,

118
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:13,200
why is there a faint smell of incense?

119
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:15,240
I feel like I've smelled it somewhere before.

120
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:17,960
What's even stranger is,

121
00:05:18,880 --> 00:05:19,720
the deceased

122
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:21,440
has already been burned like this,

123
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:22,880
how could there

124
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:24,200
still be a lingering smell of incense?

125
00:05:42,760 --> 00:05:43,160
Master Lin.

126
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:45,000
How many costumes did Madam Bai have?

127
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:46,520
Only one, of course.

128
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:48,200
Is that so?

129
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:52,280
I don't know.

130
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:55,960
I really don't know.

131
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:58,000
Qingqing.

132
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:00,400
You just said you smelled

133
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:01,400
the incense somewhere else.

134
00:06:02,280 --> 00:06:03,240
Do you know where?

135
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:07,680
On Judou and Chunxiao,

136
00:06:07,960 --> 00:06:09,440
and on Old Madam Lin.

137
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:10,240
I smelled it on all of them.

138
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:13,880
Master Lin.

139
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:15,440
It seems we need to open the coffins

140
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:17,200
to re-examine Old Madam Lin

141
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,520
and the two maids' bodies.

142
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:21,720
Inspector Huang.

143
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:23,800
The Old Madam's mourning hall

144
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,080
still needs someone to watch over it.

145
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:25,800
I won't

146
00:06:26,080 --> 00:06:27,000
bother you all anymore.

147
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:31,920
The cause of Judou and Chunxiao's deaths

148
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:33,120
is the same as the initial autopsy.

149
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:35,440
They indeed died of severe blood loss.

150
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:38,840
The Old Madam's body

151
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:39,920
also had the same scent.

152
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:42,120
Now let's see if they have it on them.

153
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:44,440
Qingqing.

154
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:45,760
Among us,

155
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:47,040
only you can distinguish this scent.

156
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:07,120
There is also...

157
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,960
Besides the same smell of blood,

158
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:15,040
there is the same fragrance.

159
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:17,320
And the closer to the body,

160
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:18,480
the stronger the scent.

161
00:07:22,640 --> 00:07:22,960
Who's there?

162
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:26,080
It's me.

163
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:27,400
Chunxing.

164
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:30,080
Come.

165
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:30,880
Come in quickly.

166
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:36,120
Why are you here?

167
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:37,680
Why were you hiding outside the door

168
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:38,600
eavesdropping on us?

169
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:39,640
No, no, no.

170
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:40,840
I didn't mean to.

171
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:42,760
I just wanted to burn some joss paper

172
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:44,480
for Judou and the others.

173
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:46,160
If you're paying respects,

174
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,080
why be so sneaky?

175
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:51,920
Judou and I

176
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:53,000
are from the same hometown.

177
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,800
Because I heard Steward Lai say

178
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:56,160
that Judou and Chunxiao

179
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:57,360
died because they desecrated

180
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:59,800
Madam Bai's favorite costume.

181
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:02,360
So he wouldn't let us pay respects to them.

182
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:03,720
This room

183
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:05,160
was sealed off because of that.

184
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:07,200
If you hadn't come,

185
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:09,080
this room wouldn't have been opened.

186
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:11,040
So,

187
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:11,920
Steward Lai...

188
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:13,280
Why would he say that?

189
00:08:16,280 --> 00:08:17,280
I don't know either.

190
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:18,920
Chunxing,

191
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:20,800
you and Judou are from the same hometown.

192
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:22,120
Do you know if,

193
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:22,960
while she was alive,

194
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,160
she had any grudges against anyone?

195
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:27,960
Then...

196
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:28,920
What about Second Madam?

197
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:30,360
I see that she usually

198
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:31,360
has quite a temper.

199
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:34,040
Second Madam is indeed

200
00:08:34,040 --> 00:08:35,320
a bit impatient with us.

201
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:36,920
But Judou once said

202
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,640
that Second Madam was very good to them.

203
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:40,040
She almost never scolded them.

204
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:43,560
I remember now.

205
00:08:44,040 --> 00:08:45,200
Before Old Madam Lin died,

206
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:46,680
she called Judou and Steward Lai

207
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:47,960
into her room

208
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,080
and talked for a while.

209
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:51,320
Steward Lai had a flushed face

210
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:52,760
when he came out of Old Madam Lin's room,

211
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:54,120
and even knocked over

212
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:55,600
the tea I brewed for her.

213
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:57,680
Later,

214
00:08:58,160 --> 00:08:59,440
Judou also ran out of

215
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:00,240
Old Madam Lin's room crying.

216
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:03,560
Do you know what they talked about?

217
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:08,080
I only know

218
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:09,680
that Judou was crying while packing her bags.

219
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:10,720
I asked her,

220
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:11,840
but she wouldn't tell me.

221
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:14,040
And Steward Lai

222
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,440
seemed to be getting ready to leave too.

223
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,200
I've told you everything I know.

224
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:21,560
You absolutely must not say

225
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:22,640
that I was the one who told you.

226
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:25,000
Okay.

227
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:25,960
You can go out first.

228
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:32,360
Do you guys think

229
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:34,360
what Chunxing said is true?

230
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:37,080
Why have I never heard Steward Lai

231
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:37,920
mention it?

232
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:40,800
This Lai Fu

233
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:42,240
is the steward of the Lin residence.

234
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,760
Since Master Lin asked him to keep the costume,

235
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:46,400
how could he not know

236
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:48,000
that Second Madam took it?

237
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,000
It seems

238
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:53,200
this Lai Fu

239
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:54,760
must be hiding something from us.

240
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:56,760
Let's go.

241
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:58,040
Let's go find him.

242
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:01,920
Inspector!

243
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:03,400
Steward Lai is dead!
